{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Jean David Blanc <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name --> | image = Jean-David Blanc.jpg | nationality = French | known_for = [[AlloCiné]], Molotov, ''Three Days in Nepal'' (book) | children = 3 | domestic_partner = [[Melissa George]] (2011–2016) | birth_place = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1968}} | occupation = Entrepreneur, film producer, writer, jazz musician, investor }}
'''Jean-David Blanc''' (born 1968) is a French entrepreneur, founder of [[AlloCiné]], [[business angel]], film producer, writer and [[jazz]] musician.<ref name=french>{{cite web|url=http://www.franceinter.fr/emission-partir-avec-jean-david-blanc|title=Jean-David Blanc|publisher=French Inter|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=evene>{{cite web|url=http://www.evene.fr/celebre/biographie/jean-david-blanc-2003987.php|title=Jean-David Blanc|publisher=Evene|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=yahoo/><ref name="IT espresso.fr">{{cite web|url=http://www.itespresso.fr/interview-jean-david-blanc-internet-television-68930.html|title=Interview Jean-David Blanc: Un Nouveau Projet À La Croisée Du Net Et De La Télévision|publisher=IT espresso.fr|author=Jérôme Bouteiller|date=16 October 2013|accessdate=18 October 2013}}</ref>
==Life and career== Blanc was born into a family of musicians; his father is the violinist [[Serge Blanc (violinist)|Serge Blanc]] and his mother is a music teacher. His younger brother, Emmanuel Blanc, is a violist with the [[Orchestre National de France]].<ref name=kimmel>{{cite web|url=http://www.kimmelcenter.org/events/notes/item/0708/OrchestreNationalFrance_notes.pdf|title=Orchestre National De France|publisher=Kimmel Center|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref> Blanc started his career in [[eBusiness]] from a young age.<ref name=evene/> At the age of 13, he designed video games for the [[Apple II]] and published articles in computer publications. At 15, he and Jean Marc Royer created Futura, a [[bulletin board system]].<ref name=evene/> Blanc founded his first IT services company, Crystal Technologies, and introduced the first electronic information service supported on Minitel for the Marlboro Racing Service the following year.<ref name=evene/><ref name=economie>{{cite web|url=http://www.transfert.net/ARCHIVES-1-08-AlloCine-sept-ans-de|title=AlloCiné, sept ans de connexion|publisher=Économie|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref> At 17, he established his first company, Concerto Telematique, which provided interactive [[Minitel]] and phone services to brands such as [[Marlboro (cigarette)|Marlboro]], [[Nissan]], [[Elf Aquitaine|Elf]] and [[Coca-Cola]].<ref name=evene/> At the age of 22, he had the idea of [[AlloCiné]], a telephone and web-based film ticketing service, and launched the company with Patrick Holzman in 1993.<ref name=evene/><ref name=economie/><ref name=screendaily>{{cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/founders-quit-as-allocine-expands-online-ticketing/405046.article|title=Founders quit as AlloCine expands online ticketing|publisher=Screen Daily|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref> After 10 years as CEO and developing [[AlloCiné]], Blanc sold the company to [[Vivendi Universal]] in 2001.<ref name=evene/><ref name=yahoo>{{cite web|url=http://au.news.yahoo.com/thewest/a/-/breaking/15337825/undercover-angel-slips-in/|title=Undercover angel slips in|publisher=The West Australian|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref>
After [[AlloCiné]], Blanc has become an active [[business angel]], consultant and strategic advisor for groups and venture capitals related to the internet and new technologies in Europe and the US.<ref name=yahoo/><ref name=cadre>{{cite web|url=http://www.cadre-dirigeant-magazine.com/actu/vie-des-affaires-business/investissements-parrains-web-francais/|title=Où investissent les parrains du Web français|publisher=Cadre et Dirigeant|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref> He has invested in start-ups such as Appsfire, [[Square Inc.]], TheCools, [[Meetic]], and Véoprint.<ref name=evene/> In addition, he mentors and sponsors the startup program at the SUPdeWEB school in Paris.<ref name=supdeweb>{{cite web|url= http://www.supdeweb.com/masteres/mastere-start-up-digitale/|title=Formation Bac + 4 / 5 – Start-Up Digitale|publisher=Sup De Web|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref>
In June 2015, Jean-David Blanc launches with [[Pierre Lescure]] and members of the prime [[AlloCiné]] team, a new online TV service called Molotov.<ref>{{Cite web|title = How A Team of Accomplished Entrepreneurs Plan To Revolutionize Your Television Experience|url = https://techcrunch.com/2015/06/18/how-a-team-of-accomplished-entrepreneurs-plan-to-revolutionize-your-television-experience/|website = TechCrunch|accessdate = 18 June 2015|first = Romain|last = Dillet}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Molotov TV – La télé. Réinventée.|url = http://www.molotov.tv/|website = Molotov TV|accessdate = 18 June 2015}}</ref>
In 2016 he was publicly accused by former partner Melissa George of physical assault against herself, which led to the termination of the relationship.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Huff Post – Melissa George Breaks Silence On Alleged Domestic Abuse In Harrowing Interview.|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/entry/melissa-george-breaks-silence-on-alleged-violent-assault_us_58cfe82ce4b0be71dcf638d2|accessdate = 20 March 2017}}</ref> They both have been condemned by the Court for mutual violence.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Paris Match (fr) - Melissa George et Jean-David Blanc condamnés|url=http://www.parismatch.com/People/Melissa-George-et-Jean-David-Blanc-condamnes-1189238|accessdate= 26 October 2017}}</ref>
==Other works and professional activities== Blanc has been a musician from a young age. He studied harmony and improvisation with the pedagogue [[:fr:Robert_Kaddouch|Robert Kaddouch]], and studied jazz piano at the American School of Modern Music in Paris, France.<ref name=french/><ref name=evene/> He has worked with actors and directors on different films and projects, and produced the 2005 film, Cavalcade.<ref name=evene/><ref name=imdb>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0427047/?ref_=nm_flmg_prd_1|title=Cavalcade|publisher=IMDb|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref> In 2012, Blanc authored his first book, Three Days in Nepal, which recounted Blanc's experience of a 2011 [[paramotoring]] accident that left him trapped in the mountains of [[Nepal]].<ref name=evene/><ref name=France5>{{cite web|url=http://www.france5.fr/emissions/c-a-vous/c-l-info-jean-david-blanc-le-miracule-de-l-himalaya_6453|title=C L'Info : Jean-David Blanc, Le Miraculé De L'Himalaya|publisher=France 5|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=himalayan>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehimalayantimes.com/rssReference.php?headline=Paramotor+pilot+returns+favour&NewsID=274282|title=Paramotor pilot returns favour|publisher=The Himalayan Times|accessdate=30 September 2013}}</ref>
