'''Otto Heilmann''' (22 August 1888, in [[Munich]] &ndash; 19 August 1945, at [[Schwaneck Castle]], [[Pullach]]) was a German [[architect]] and [[general contractor|contractor]].

After studying civil engineering, he joined his father's construction company [[Heilmann & Littmann]], as a proxy holding manager. Later he joined the supervisory board.

